title: Bug 109350: Output parameter does not display in data set dialog
description: When calling the stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, there is no data returned. The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: When calling the stored procedure and retrieving the query result from the Oracle database, the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog when retrieving the query result from the Oracle database.
SR:
1. Connect to an Oracle database.
2. Call a stored procedure that retrieves a query result.
3. Open the edit data set dialog.
4. Verify if the output parameter is displayed in the dialog.
